easyRNG
------------------------------------------
A lightweight and easy-to-use library that wraps C++11's random number
generators, making them available from C and Fortran.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libeasyRNG-devel-1.2-1bl2
  libeasyRNG0-1.2-1bl2
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cygport-0.37.6-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-fortran-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/tschoonj/easyRNG

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/tschoonj/easyRNG/archive/refs/tags/easyRNG-1.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack easyRNG-1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./easyRNG-1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/easyRNG-1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/easyRNG-1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyRNG0-1.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyRNG-devel-1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(easyRNG)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/easyRNG.README
  /usr/share/doc/easyRNG/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/easyRNG/README.md

(libeasyRNG0)
  /usr/bin/cygeasyRNG-0.dll

(libeasyRNG-devel)
  /usr/include/easyRNG/easy_randist.h
  /usr/include/easyRNG/easy_rng.h
  /usr/include/easyRNG/easyrng.mod
  /usr/lib/libeasyRNG.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/easyRNG.pc

